      "content": "Instead of just a basic wrap, you need to apply firm, consistent compression using an elastic bandage, wrapping it from the toes up past the ankle, but never so tight that your toes turn blue or tingle. While doing this, you must also ensure you are elevating it above the level of your heart at all times—prop it up on pillows while you rest. If you notice any increased throbbing or numbness after 48 hours, you must stop the home treatment immediately and seek professional help.",
